==Calvinist==

So, was he a calvinist?  If he was Lutheran instead, change WPCalvinism above to WPLutheranism

:yes, a Calvinist.  If he had been a Lutheran, the princes probably would have supported him.  But Calvinism was a heresy then, not an approved form in the Augsburg Peace 1555.[[User:Auntieruth55|Auntieruth55]] ([[User talk:Auntieruth55|talk]]) 02:04, 9 July 2009 (UTC)

==Military History==

added template because his notability rests in large part upon his triggering the Cologne War.[[User:Auntieruth55|Auntieruth55]] ([[User talk:Auntieruth55|talk]]) 02:44, 7 October 2009 (UTC)
